The paper deals with concept recognition tasks in computer vision, which is a subfield of computer science. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely category. The paper also discusses multiple kernel learning techniques, which are related to machine learning and optimization, suggesting that cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely categories. Additionally, the paper deals with image classification and annotation, which are related to multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR), respectively, making them less likely but still possible categories.
